[[File:Lostmauth Lair sanctum.png|thumb|right|350px|A group of adventurers standing before Lostmauth within his innermost sanctum.]]
During the 1480s [[DR]],{{ToD-time}} Lostmauth granted the [[Cult of the Dragon]] admittance into his lair. After acquiring the ''[[Red Dragon Mask]]'', the cult's leader [[Severin Silrajin]] appeared before Lostmauth and the two appeared to strike a bargain. Severin offered Lostmauth some form of tribute and in return, the red dragon would destroy the city of [[Neverwinter]].

Fortunately for Neverwinter and its people, Lostmauth was slain shortly thereafter by a band of adventurers that included [[Alaeros Margaster]], [[Nymmestra Durothil]], [[Barrowin Undurr]], and [[Talon Everhale]].{{Cite web/Tyranny of Dragons: Online Comic 4}}{{ToD-Lost}}
